reviewText: Best Puss in boots i think. it was quircky funny and entertaining as a kid back in my days, decades ago. I'm glad its here can't wait to view it again. This time on DVD!

I have loved this version since I was a kid and was glad to find it streaming here! Tracey Ullman's narration, especially in her hyperbolic French accent, is funny and strange. I think it's a good test for kids today to watch after living in a world of hyper-real Pixar/Disney/Dreamworks productions. There is no animation, just a panning across of illustration. It is simple and lovely.
Poor quality. Poor narration. The kids thought it was boring. Didn't even make it through the whole film. Don't bother.
